\pard\plain \ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24 Others think it is an ethnic term, connected with Eber, the last ancestor in the line of Shem before the earth is divided (10:21\endash 25). The latter is the preferred meaning based on the following: (1) The form (}{\f0\fs24\i1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u703\'3Fi\u7687\'3Fr\u238\'EE}{\f0\fs24 ) consists of }{\f0\fs24\i1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u703\'3Fe\u7687\'3Fer}{\f0\fs24  + a gentilic }{\f0\fs24\i1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u238\'EE}{\f0\fs24 , like Israeli or Israelite from Israel; (2) this form is appropriate with the proper name Eber, not with }{\f0\fs24\i1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u703\'3Fapiru}{\f0\fs24 ; (3) the term always occurs in opposition to other ethnic groups, especially the Egyptians and Philistines; (4) though landless, the other characteristics of Abraham do not fit the }{\f0\fs24\i1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u703\'3Fapiru}{\f0\fs24 . The Bible ascribes the term only to Abraham and his descendants to show that they are the legitimate descendants of Shem through Eber.\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0  Waltke, B. K., & Fredricks, C. J. (2001). \\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosres/genesiswaltke?ref=Bible.Ge14.13&off=645&ctx=less+(see+Gen.+23).+~Others+think+it+is+a"}{\fldrslt\f2\fs24\b0\i1\ul\ulc0\cf3 Genesis: a commentary\\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0  (p. 231). Grand Rapids, MI: Zondervan.\\end_Scrv_fn\}}}